@node The Age of Gods Scenario, Novice Scenario, Scenarios, Scenarios
@subsubsection The Age of Gods Scenario

The Age of Gods scenario takes place at the time in Olympia history when
the Imperial and Mandor empires were re-discovering each other.  (See
@ref{Appendix - History}.)  Players have the choice of joining the Imperial Empire,
the Mandor Empire, or the Pen.  The game is won when one nation conquers
the rest (see @ref{Winning the Game}.

@node Novice Scenario, The Never-Ending Kingdom Scenario, The Age of Gods Scenario, Scenarios
@subsubsection Novice Scenario

The novice scenario takes place in a small world with only one nation.
Players are limited to 12 turns of free play.  This scenario is intended
to give the new TAG player some experience with the game.

@node The Never-Ending Kingdom Scenario, The Eight Kings Scenario, Novice Scenario, Scenarios
@subsubsection The Never-Ending Kingdom Scenario

The Never-Ending Kingdom scenario takes place long after the Age of
Gods.  Olympia has been unified into a single nation, which after a long
fall into barbarism is now setting out to explore and conquer the world.
All skills are available to all players.  This is an open-ended
scenario.

@node The Eight Kings Scenario,  , The Never-Ending Kingdom Scenario, Scenarios
@subsubsection The Eight Kings Scenario

Eight islands in the Endless Sea surround an extinct volcano.  On each
island reigns a single king.  Prophets have foretold a great disaster if
the islands are not unified under a single king by the turn of the
millenium in ten years (80 turns).  Unfortunately, no king is willing to
let another wear his crown...

This scenario is limited to eight players.  The game ends when one
player is the only player to occupy any castle for three consecutive
turns.  If no one succeeds in 80 turns, the game ends and no one is
declared winner.

The Eight Kings scenario uses a number of variant rules:

@enumerate
@item 
Each player will start alone on an island.  No neighboring island will
be closer than 2 ocean provinces.  At least one neighbor island will be
2 ocean provinces away.
@item
Each player designs their own start island, customizing this map:

@example
@group
