d 		desert
p 		plain
: 		swamp
&		forest
.		ocean
@end group
@end example
The customized map must contain at least 18 ocean squares, and at most
50% mountainous coastline.  The GM reserves the right to refuse a map.

The player also indicates the location of a start city and a castle.

The island may be rotated 90 or 180 degrees when placed on the world map. 
@item
Initial city starts with 10K population and 4 towers.
@item
The first noble will start in the city.
@item
Each player will be a separate nation.
@item
No Mage/Priest antipathy (see @ref{Mage/Priest Antipathy}).
@item
Players will pick 3 normal skill schools they will never be able
to learn.
@item
No new castles can be built.
@item
CLAIM of fighting troops can only be used by a castle owner.
@item 
FORM may be used in a castle or a city.
@end enumerate

In addition, each player will start with 200 noble points.  Prior to the
first turn of the game, players will use the points to (1) select a
religion, and (2) purchase CLAIM items.  Any unused points will be
available to the player during the game.

Each player will be able to learn only one religion.  Religions will be
selected by blind auction.  Each player will submit to the GM an ordered
list of religions and how many NPs the player is willing to bid on that
