@section Skills
@display
  No profit grows where is no pleasure taken; 
  In brief, sir, study what you most affect.

                   William Shakespeare

@end display


Skills represent knowledge that Olympian nobles may know.
Shipbuilding, thievery, kidnaping, training soldiers, castle building,
mixing potions, and forging magical artifacts are just a few of the
possible actions which skills allow a noble to perform.

@c @group
Skills are organized into categories.  Before a noble can learn any of
the skills in a category he must first learn the category skill.  The
category skills are:

@example
@group
num  name                       time to learn
---  ----                       -------------
1000  Shipcraft                  one week
1100  Combat                     one week
1200  Stealth                    two weeks
1300  Persuasion                 two weeks
1400  Construction               one week
1500  Alchemy                    two weeks
1600  Forestry                   one week
1700  Mining                     one week
1800  Trading                    one week
1900  Ranger                     one week
@end group
@end example

There are also six schools of magic and eight religions.  For more
details on learning and casting magical spells, see @ref{Magical Arts}.
For more details on religion skills, see @ref{Religion}.  Note that
magicians cannot learn religion skills, and priests and their followers
cannot learn magic skills.

Most skills are invoked with the @samp{@code{use} @var{skill}} order.
Specific information about arguments to @code{use} and and requirements
or limitations for using all Olympia skills may be found in
@ref{Appendix - Skill Dictionary}.

To begin study of a skill requires the following:

@itemize @bullet
@item A source of instruction (possibly).
@item Payment of a fee for necessary materials.
@end itemize

To complete the study of a skill requires the following:

@itemize @bullet
@item Payment of any necessary noble points.
@end itemize

The following sections describe the process of learning new skills in
more detail.

