@node Hints, Offenses against realism, Miscellaneous, Miscellaneous
@section Hints

Here are some starting hints for new players.

@table @dfn
@item (1)
Don't try to be self-sufficient.  Contact your fellow players and
work with them.  There is a huge advantage to playing as part of a
"team". 

@item (2)
NPs are the most important resource in the game.  Use them wisely.
Most nobles can be contract loyalty.  At the very least, wait
until your initial contract loyalty wears off before you "oath" a
noble.  By then you might have lots of gold!

@item (3)
Don't spend too much of your starting gold before you establish some new
sources of income.  Here are the common ways to earn money in TAG:

@table @dfn
@item
Taxes/Tariffs: high income, but difficult to establish.
@item
Fishing: steady income, needs a port city.
@item
Inns: low income, ties up a noble.
@item
Pots/Baskets: low income, lots of competition, easy.
@item
Treasure Hunting: potentially high rewards, dangerous.
@item
Trade: high income, difficult to establish.
@end table
@item (4)
The Age of Gods is not vanilla Olympia!  Check the rules before you
assume something works the same in both games.  In particular, The Age
