This skill permits a character to build a mine shaft.

A mine is a deep shaft or tunnel which allows workers to extract
valuable resources from the earth, such as iron and gold.  Mine shafts
must be built in mountain provinces or in another mine shaft; there may
be at most one mine shaft in a location.  A mine shaft is built with the
"build shaft" command.  To build a mine shaft, a noble must know [1703]
Deepen Mine Shaft.  Building a mine requires at least 3 workers and 500
worker-days of effort.

When a mine shaft is completed, it will be "down" from the location in
which it was built.  Each mine shaft descends 100 feet, so that the
initial mine shaft in a location goes down 100 feet; a mine shaft
built in that mine shaft descends to 200 feet, and so on.  E.g., 

@example
@group
