trade good in a market.  By intimating that a product is inferior, had
bad side-effects, and similar means, the merchant will discourage the
buying public, driving the price of the trade good down from 6 to 8
percent.  The price decrease persists until something changes it.

This skill must be used in the market where <good> is being
traded.  The price for a good cannot be driven lower than half the
base price of the good.

This skill can only be used on items sold or bought by the market
itself, i.e., it cannot be used on nobles, and it only works if the good
is currently being traded.  For example, consider this interaction:

@example
@group
8: > use 1803 94
8: That good is not traded here.
@end group
@end example

