strongly built man of advancing years, with a wild mane of white hair. 
Priests of Eres typically build their temples near the sea and often
serve on sailing ships.  It is said that a ship with a Priest of Eres on
it will never capsize or be lost in a storm.  Certainly it is true that
Priests of Eres have saved many a ship with their powerful prayers to
control the weather.

Temples to Eres must be built in ocean provinces (on islands), or in
coastal provinces next to the ocean.  Attempts to consecrate temples
elsewhere will fail.

Priests of Eres are the only nobles who can see individual storms.
Other nobles will see only the effects of storms (e.g., rain or fog).

