@node  Combat Artifacts, Leadership of Men, Appendix - Magical Artifacts, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Combat Artifacts

Combat artifacts grant bonuses to attack or defense during combat.  Some
artifacts grant specific bonuses (e.g., a +5 bonus to defense against
missile attacks), while others grant general bonuses (e.g., a +5 bonus
to defense against all attacks).  Some artifacts grant the bonus to the
noble bearing the artifact, while others grant the bonus to the men he
directly commands.

When a combat artifact is identified, it will reveal the bonuses it
grants.  For example:

@display
8: > identify atq
8: [atq] Combat Artifact, +5 affects: personal melee attack
@end display

The bonus is added to the noble's attack or defense value, as
appropriate.  For artifacts that apply to the men he commands, the bonus
is added to their attack or defense values, as appropriate.

It is possible to have artifacts with multiple bonuses:

@display
8: > identify atq 8
8: [atq] Combat Artifact, +5 bonus affects: personal melee attack, 
8: commanded men missile defense
@end display

This artifact would give the men commanded by the noble +5 on both his
personal melee attacks and on defense for the men in his command against
missile attacks.

Only the best artifact for a particular bonus is applied.  For example,
if a noble had two artifacts, one of which provided a +5 bonus for
missile attacks, and the other a +8 bonus for missile attacks, then only
the latter would apply.

Here is the list of possible bonuses in a combat artifact:

@table @asis
@item personal melee attack
This bonus improves the user's melee attack.
@item personal missile attack
This bonus improves the user's missile attack.  If he has no missile
attack, it has no effect.
@item personal special attack
This bonus improves the user's special attacks.  If he has no special
attack, it has no effect.  The bonus only applies to special attacks
that use the "attack versus defense" resolution.
@item personal melee defense
This bonus improves the user's defense against melee attacks.
@item personal missile defense
This bonus improves the user's defense against missile attacks.
@item personal special defense
This bonus improves the user's defense against special attacks.  The
bonus only applies to special attacks that use the "attack versus
defense" resolution.
@item commanded men melee attack
This bonus improves the melee attacks of the men the noble directly commands.
@item commanded men missile attack
This bonus improves the missile attacks of the men the noble directly commands.
@item commanded men special attack
This bonus improves the special attacks of the men the noble directly commands.
@item commanded men melee defense
This bonus improves the defense against melee attacks of the men the
noble directly commands.
@item commanded men missile defense
This bonus improves the defense against missile attacks of the men the
noble directly commands.
@item commanded men special defense
This bonus improves the defense against special attacks of the men the
noble directly commands.
@end table

Rumors tell of an exceedingly rare artifact called the "Ring of Heroes"
that gives a +50 bonus to every aspect of combat.

@node  Leadership of Men, Beast Enchantment, Combat Artifacts, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Leadership of Men

This artifact increases the number of men a noble can control in combat. 

@node  Beast Enchantment, Safety from Attack, Leadership of Men, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Beast Enchantment

This artifact increases the number of beasts a noble can control in combat. 

@node  Safety from Attack, Improved Attack, Beast Enchantment, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Safety from Attack

This artifact protects the owner from attack by a specific type of
monster, e.g., orcs.  It only protects the owner from random wilderness
attacks, not from attacks by other players, or from elves in Faery.

@node  Improved Attack, Improved Defense, Safety from Attack, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Improved Attack

This artifact improves the attack of a specific type of soldier in the
owner's control, e.g., +5 attack for pikemen.

@node  Improved Defense, Safety at Sea, Improved Attack, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Improved Defense

This artifact improves the defense for a specific type of soldier in the
owner's control, e.g., +5 attack for pikemen.

@node  Safety at Sea, Defensive Terrain Enchantment, Improved Defense, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Safety at Sea

If the captain of a boat possesses this artifact, the boat will be
protected from all the dangers of sailing, i.e., running aground,
capsizing, becoming lost, etc.

@node  Defensive Terrain Enchantment, Fast Terrain, Safety at Sea, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Defensive Terrain Enchantment

This artifact improves the defense of a noble and any men he commands in
a particular terrain.  The artifact improves their defense by a
percentage, e.g., a +15 bonus Defensive Terrain Enchantment (woods) will
improve a noble and his men's defensive values by 15% while they are in
woods. 

@node  Fast Terrain, Speed Use, Defensive Terrain Enchantment, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Fast Terrain

The owner of this artifact and the men he commands move more quickly
into the specified terrain.  Each bonus point reduces travel time by 1
day, a +2 bonus Fast Terrain (woods) artifact speeds travel into woods
by 2 days.  This artifact affects only movement with the @ref{move}
and @ref{attack} commands, not flying or sailing.

@node  Speed Use, Hellring, Fast Terrain, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Speed Use

This artifact reduces the amount of time required to use a particular
skill, e.g., -1 day to use Extract venom from ratspider [1530].

@node  Hellring, Elfstone, Speed Use, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Hellring

This artifact grants the noble personal safety in Hades.  The noble will
not be attacked by daemons or undead, and he will not suffer the usual
life-draining effects of Hades.  This protection does not extend to
nobles stacked with the protected noble.  The noble (but not others in
his stack) is also given free entrance to Hades.

@node  Elfstone, Hard Workers, Hellring, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Elfstone

This artifact grants the noble personal safety in Faery.  This
protection does not extend to men in his control or to nobles stacked
with the protected noble.  This artifact may also be used (@ref{use}) to
open a faery hill.  This artifact has a limited number of uses, and when
exhausted, no longer provides protection in Faery.

@node  Hard Workers, Improved Income, Elfstone, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Hard Workers

This artifact improves the output of any workers controlled by the
owner.  The artifact will improve their production by a percentage,
e.g., a +15 bonus Hard Workers ring will improve the output of workers
by 15%.

@node  Improved Income, Fast Learning, Hard Workers, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Improved Income

This artifact will improve the income generated by a structure (e.g., a
temple or an inn) by a percentage.

@node  Fast Learning, Fast Teaching, Improved Income, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Fast Learning

This artifact reduces the time a noble requires to learn a new skill
by one or two days.

@node  Fast Teaching, Fast Training, Fast Learning, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Fast Teaching

This artifact reduces the time a noble requires to teach a new skill to
students by one or two days (that is, the students reduce the time they
require to learn the skill if the teacher possesses this artifact).

@node  Fast Training, Destroy Monster, Fast Teaching, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Fast Training

This artifact allows a noble to train two of a particular unit each day
rather than one, e.g., a noble with Fast Training (elite archers) would
train two elite archers each day instead of one.  Note that the noble
must still have the necessary ingredients (e.g., two archers and two
elvish arrows).

@node  Destroy Monster, Riding, Fast Training, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Destroy Monster

When used (@ref{use}), this artifact destroys all the monsters of the
designated type in the user's location, e.g., an artifact of Destroy
Monster orc would destroy all orcs.  This artifact has a limited number
of uses.

@node  Riding, Flying, Destroy Monster, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Riding

This artifact permits the owner to move at riding speed.  It is rated
for capacity (between 100 and 500 units of weight).

@node  Flying, Carry Great Loads, Riding, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Flying

This artifact permits the owner to fly.  It is rated for capacity
(between 100 and 500 units of weight).

This artifact can only operate continuously for fifteen days, so only
fifteen days in a row can be spent flying over the ocean.  At the end of
the fifteenth day, the artifact will cease to function, and the entire
stack will plunge into the sea, killing all of the stack's nobles.

Any arrival at a land or ship location will allow the artifact to be
stopped and restarted, renewing the fifteen day limit.

@node Carry Great Loads, Protection from Skill, Flying, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Carry Great Loads

This artifact permits the owner to carry additional weight at walking
speeds.  It is rated for capacity between 100 and 500 units of weight.

@node  Protection from Skill, Shield Location, Carry Great Loads, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Protection from Skill

This artifact protects the owner from uses of a particular skill.  For
example, a noble in possession of "Protection from Skill (Receive vision
[2434])" could not be visioned.

@node  Shield Location, Power Jewel, Protection from Skill, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Shield Location

This artifact prevents any magical scrying or visions in the owner's location.

@node  Power Jewel, Summon Aid, Shield Location, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Power Jewel

When used (@ref{use}), this artifact grants the user additional aura or
mana.  This artifact has a limited number of uses.

@node  Summon Aid, Reduced Maintenance, Power Jewel, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Summon Aid

When used (@ref{use}), this artifact summons aid of the indicated type
and number, adding those units to the owner's inventory.  For example,
an artifact "Summon Aid, 12 soldiers" would add 12 soldiers to the
user's inventory.  This artifact has a limited number of uses.

@node  Reduced Maintenance, Improve Bargaining, Summon Aid, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Reduced Maintenance

This artifact reduces the maintenance costs of a noble by the specified
percentage, e.g., a +20 bonus Reduced Maintenance artifact reduces
maintenance costs by 20%.

@node  Improve Bargaining, Weightlessness, Reduced Maintenance, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Improve Bargaining

This artifact reduces the price a noble pays for goods in a city or
guild market by the specified percentage, e.g., a +20 bonus Improve
Bargaining artifact reduces prices by 20%.  This applies only to goods
sold by the city or guild (not other players) and the discount is
applied only at the end of the sale (i.e., not when the market is
determining the highest bidder).

@node  Weightlessness, Increased Healing, Improve Bargaining, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Weightlessness

This artifact reduces the weight of a noble and his inventory by the
indicated amount.

@node  Increased Healing, Protection from Sickness, Weightlessness, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Increased Healing

This artifact increases the amount a noble heals by the indicated
amount. 

@node  Protection from Sickness, Restore Life, Increased Healing, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Protection from Sickness

A noble possessing this artifact will never fall ill.

@node  Restore Life, Teleport, Protection from Sickness, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Restore Life

One of the most powerful of the ancient artifacts, this artifact
restores a noble to life after his death.  The noble will be resurrected
in the starting city of his nation, and will have no possessions.  This
artifact has a limited number of charges.

@node  Teleport, Orb of Scrying, Restore Life, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Teleport

When used (@ref{use}), this artifact teleports the user and his
possessions to a location designated by the user, e.g., if [atq] was an
artifact of Teleport, then the command "use atq h24" would attempt to
teleport the user to location [h24].  This artifact has an indicated
weight limited and a limited number of charges.

@node  Orb of Scrying, Crown of Control, Teleport, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Orb of Scrying

This artifact may be used to gain visions of characters, items, or
places.  Issue the order USE <artifact> <target> to scry the given
target with the artifact.  The artifact has a limited number of charges.

Unlike magical and religious scrying skills, the Orb of Scrying work
across oceans.

@node  Crown of Control, Staff of the Sun, Orb of Scrying, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Crown of Control

This artifact may be used to gain control of a stack of monsters.  Each
artifact is tuned to one particular type of monster and has a limited
number of charges.  For example, a Crown of Control (orcs) may be used
to seize control of a stack of orcs.  To seize control of a stack of
monsters, the user must be in the same location as the stack and issue
the order USE <artifact> <target>.

Once a player has seized control of a stack of monsters, the new unit
will appear in his turn report and can be treated in many ways like any
other noble.  The new unit will be of loyalty "NPC" and will not require
pay or any other incentives.  However, the commands that controlled
monster units may execute are limited to the following:

@table @asis
@item accept
@item admit
@item attack 
@item banner
@item behind
@item contact
@item default
@item defend
@item drop
@item execute
@item flag
@item get
@item give
@item hostile
@item move
@item maxpay
@item name
@item neutral
@item pay
@item pillage
@item promote
@item raze
@item seek
@item stack
@item stop
@item take
@item terrorize
@item unstack
@item wait
@end table

In combat, a controlled monster unit can command the same number of men
as a garrison unit (i.e., 20 men on attack and 40 on defense).  A
controlled monster unit can command any number of beasts of the same
type, but none of any other type (e.g., an orc unit could command any
number of orcs, but no centaurs).

@node Staff of the Sun,  , Crown of Control, Appendix - Magical Artifacts
@appendixsec Staff of the Sun
The Staff of the Sun is a mythical artifact of great power.  Broken into
eight pieces in a long-forgotten time, it has the power in the hands of
priest to utterly destroy all magicians, and in the hands of a magician
the power to utterly destroy all priests.  Consequently both priests and
magicians are actively seeking to rebuild the Staff of the Sun.

If a priest holds all eight pieces of the Staff of the Sun at the end of
a month, then the power of the staff will destroy all magicians.
Likewise, if a magician holds all eight pieces of the Staff of the Sun
at the end of a month, then the staff will destroy all priests.  Once it
destroys all priests or magicians, the Staff of the Sun destroys itself,
although legend holds that it can never be completely destroyed.

The pieces of the Staff of the Sun also grant piety bonuses to priests,
help mages regenerate aura, and can be used to discover other pieces
of the Staff.

Each month the Times prints a summary of the pieces of the Staff of the
Sun:

@example
  Staff of the Sun Summary
  ------------------------

  * Five pieces of the Staff of the Sun are held by monsters.
    * One piece is held somewhere on Mandoria.
    * One piece is held somewhere on Catarack Island.
    * One piece is held somewhere on Imperia.
    * One piece is held somewhere on Imperia.
    * One piece is held somewhere on Mandoria.
  * One piece of the Staff of the Sun is held by priests.
    * One piece is held somewhere on Imperia.
  * One piece of the Staff of the Sun is held by magicians.
    * One piece is held somewhere on Mandoria.
@end example

@node Appendix - Command Preprocessing, Appendix - Output Formats, Appendix - Magical Artifacts, Top
@appendix Appendix - Command Preprocessing

When you submit orders to TAG, the game can run those orders through a
preprocessor for you.  The preprocessor can convert orders like

@example
        give Maldor peasants
@end example

into (for example)

@example
        give 5499 10
@end example

This permits you to write your orders in a more English-like (and
perhaps, more error-free) format.

To use this facility, you must include the keyword "preprocess" on the
subject line of the mail you send to TAG.

The preprocessor currently includes the following aliases:

@example
	#define gold 1
	#define golds 1
	#define peasant 10
	#define peasants 10
	#define worker 11
	#define workers 11
	#define soldier 12
	#define soldiers 12
	#define archer 13
	#define archers 13
	#define knight 14
	#define knights     14
	#define elite_guard 15
	#define elite_guards 15
	#define paladin 15
	#define paladins 15
	#define pikeman 16
	#define pikemans 16
	#define blessed_soldier 17
