@appendixsec RAW Format

RAW format is similar to TEXT format with several exceptions.

First, RAW format includes the embedded tags of TAGS format.  Second,
RAW format is not "line-wrapped".  Lines in RAW format may be longer
than 80 characters.  Third, the RAW format uses the tilde character (~)
to indicate a non-breaking space.  Finally, each line in RAW format
starts with a header.  The format of the header is:

@example
<unit identifier>:<indent>/<secondary indent>:<day>:<line>
@end example

@table @asis
@item <unit identifier>
The unit which produced this line of output.  Currently the unit
identifier is only used in the garrison log.
@item <indent>
The number of spaces to indent this line when displaying it in TEXT
format.
@item <secondary indent>
The number of spaces to indent any continuation lines if this line must
be "wrapped".
@item <day>
The day of the month for this line of output.
@end table

Here is a (contrived) example of a line of RAW format output:

@example
:0/3:17:Eristan Guardenriver~[n6l], Imperial Empire, duke, with five~workers, eight~sailors, arrived from [x1x] Imperial Plains.
@end example

and here is how it might be rendered in TEXT format:

@example
17: Eristan Guardenriver [n6l], Imperial Empire, duke, with, five workers,
17:   eight sailors, arrived from [x1x] Imperial Plains.
@end example

